        "name": "chi_0(k) exponential-continuity pin",
        "statement": "chi_0(k) = (-1)^k = zeta_10^{5k} for the CONTROL tower's fiber character at the z=0 fixed point, obtained by ASSUMING the fiber character is exponential in the weight parameter (chi_0(w) = e^{i*w*phase} for a SINGLE fixed phase) and anchoring at the banked doublet value chi_0(1/5)=e^{i pi/5}. Dimension-count and the W^5/W^10 group-structure constraints alone do NOT pin chi_0(k) -- any mu in mu_10 satisfies them. This exponential-continuity assumption cannot be independently verified from the holonomy side without route 1's internal cocycle data (cellES, deliberately not read). FLAGGED, not silently resolved."
