        "statement": "zeta_5 = zeta_10^2 (angle +2pi/5) is chosen as the base rotation multiplier at the z=0 fixed point for the class selected by trace=phi; the opposite assignment (z=0 <-> z=infinity swapped) would relabel m -> d-m within each grade but does not change any multiplicity table (verified: the tables are symmetric under complex conjugation j -> -j, see gate 4's self-consistency spot check), so this choice is convention-free in its effect on the reported multiplicities."
      }
    ],
    "self_correction_log": [
      "First run of this script: gate 4 (Galois consistency) FAILED for PRIMARY at every grade (CONTROL passed). Root cause: primary_exponents_conjugate() initially kept the (F1,F2) doublet shift fixed at {+1,-1} while only flipping the base-rotation exponent, silently assuming the doublet's own eigenvalues zeta_10^{+-1} were Galois-fixed. They are not: sigma_3 (j -> 3j, the lift of sqrt5 -> -sqrt5) sends zeta_10^{+-1} -> zeta_10^{+-3} (matching sigma_3(phi) = -1/phi = 2cos(3 pi/5)). Fixed by using shift {+3,-3} for the conjugate doublet; gate 4 then passes at every grade 0..40. Reported here as evidence the gate is a live check, not a rubber stamp."
    ]
